complaints.summary: The contact owns a 2016 Cadillac ATS. The contact stated that the message "Service Air Bag" was displayed, and the passenger's side seat belt warning light was illuminated. The vehicle was not diagnosed or repaired. The dealer and the manufacturer were not notified of the failure. The failure mileage was unknown.

When driving at around 40-50mph you can feel that the car has a shudder vibration. Took the car into Cadillac where they are informing me that it is the torque converter that needs replacement. No warning lights. If not fixed can lead to transmission failure.

I’ve only had this vehicle for about 2 years now. I purchased it off of Carvana and had 30 days I could’ve returned the vehicle if there was issues. When I first got it, I noticed the vehicles gas pedal would shutter a tad while going up a hill or at a higher speed like on the highway. It would also jolt a little while taking off but when I took it to the dealership they were saying everything is normal and I believed everything was fine since there was no lights on the dash, it was my first time ever buying a car myself, and I had no reason not to trust them. The vehicle is now at a little less than 85,000 miles and I can’t drive it because of how bad it’s jerking, I did a little more research and come to find out this is a huge issue with GMs vehicles transmissions within that years range however my vehicle in particular isn’t on that list. The CTS and i believe even a few ATS Vs were on there but mine is doing the same exact behaviors as they’re describing. If there’s any way you guys can help me out it would honestly be a blessing

The contact owned a 2016 Cadillac ATS. The contact stated while driving 40-50 MPH and entering the expressway, she engaged the turn signal and verified that the road was cleared. The contact stated that while she was making the turn, an 18-wheeler truck suddenly hit the vehicle, causing the vehicle to crash into another vehicle. The contact stated that the vehicle was hit three times and spun onto the median, where the vehicle continued to spin until it hit the fence. The contact stated that her sister was occupying the front passenger's seat at the time of the accident. The air bags failed to deploy. Both the contact and her sister were transported to the hospital by emergency units. The contact stated that she sustained injuries on the left side of her body. The contact sustained severe pain on the left shoulder, left arm, left wrist, lower back, on and the neck down to under the shoulder blade. The contact's sister sustained injuries on the right side of the body. The contact sister sustained severe pain in the head, the ear, the right hip, the lower back, the abdomen, and the neck. A police report was filed. The vehicle was towed and totaled. The dealer and the manufacturer were not notified of the failure. The failure mileage was approximately 61,000.

Transmission drags. When stopping the car jerks bad and sometimes proceeds to accelerate. When at a stop auto start has a hard jerk I reported this problem to Cadillac dealership when I first got the car. They claim they couldn't find an issue. The touch pad goes out frequently.

Reporting a case for GM recall N182161890. I bought my vehicle in 2022. I was informed that my car had all the recalls completed on that vehicle. My vehicle had exactly what this recall was for happen to it on 10/20/23. After contacting Cadillac, they informed me that this recall was never completed on my vehicle. Cadillac then told me that this recall was expired so it can no longer be completed. They said that the recall expired on 11/30/2020. I was under the impression that recalls do not expire, especially ones that can cause lose of power steering and could lead to collision or injury. Cadillac told me it expired because it was a "Customer Satisfaction Program" recall and not a "Product Safety" recall. I'm confused on how the lose of steering is not a product safety issue. Cadillac is unwilling to fix the recall at this time, even though they have confirmed it had never been completed.

My back glass on my 2016 Cadillac ATS shattered on 3-10-2023. It looks like it got hot from the defroster lines as it shattered every inch of the back glass and separated from the seals. I contacted Cadillac and they started Case #9-9552142107. I had the car inspected at my dealership on 3-11-23. They filled out the report on this case number to support the findings of a current recall already in place.  Recall date 2015-09-03 Recall no.15V558000 General Motors LLC (GM) is recalling certain model year 2013-2016 Cadillac ATS sedan vehicles manufactured April 23, 2012, to September 2, 2015. In the affected vehicles, the coil antenna module that powers the rear defogger system may generate excessive heat due to excessive cycling or continuous operation. When I contacted Cadillac they said I needed to contact NHTSA with the info to have my car put on the recall
CUE screen cracked and is unresponsive and now handsfree safety options don't work.

When driving, I accidentaley hit a curb on the front left rim and the side air bags deployed. There was no damage to vehicle other than hitting the rim. I want to know if there is a recall on this or if there has been any other incidents of this kind. The only deployed air bags were the side ones by the windows The front air bags did not deploy. I need answers to why the car deplyed air bags when it was a curb check and no physical damage to the car? Is there any recalls on this?

THE GAS FUEL TANK CONTINUOUSLY STOPS EVERY TIME YOU ARE PUMPING GAS. SO IT TAKES VERY LONG TO FILL UP THE TANK.   MY CENTER ELECTRICAL SCREEN FOR THE RADIO, BLUETOOTH, ETC DOESN'T WORK. I PAID EXTRA FOR THE FEATURE AND IT DOESN'T WORK.

DROVE MY CAR ON THE HIGHWAY AND THE BRAKES FAILED. I APPLIED ALL OF MY FORCE TO GET THE CAR TO STOP. THIS IS THE SECOND TIME THE BRAKES FAILED WHILE DRIVING ON THE HIGHWAY IN LESS THAN 14 MONTHS. HAD IT REPAIRED THE FIRST TIME. IT HAD NO BRAKE ASSIST AND A CRACKED PCV VALVE. THE VACUUM PUMP AND HOSE TO BOOSTER WAS REPLACED. 14 MONTHS LATER IT HAPPENED AGAIN.

THE RADIO SCREEN IS CRACKING FROM THE INSIDE OF THE SCREEN I'M GETTING A SPIDERWEB EFFECT THAT IS NOT ALLOWING ME TO SEE THE SCREEN. CAN'T SEE THE SPEED OF MY AC FAN BECASUE I CAN'T SEE THE SCREEN, CAN'T CHANGE TO BLUETOOTH BECAUSE I CAN'T SEE THE SCREEN, CAN'T USE MY NAVIGATION SYSTEM THAT I PAID EXTRA FOR BECAUSE I CAN'T SEE THE SCREEN DUE TO THE SPIDERWEB EFFECT. THERE WAS A SHUDDER TO THE VEHICLE WHILE IN MOTION AND IT LURCHES FORWARD LIKE IT SKIPS GEARS WHEN GOING FROM REVERSE INTO DRIVE AND OFTEN FROM INCREASE SPEED

THE CAR MAY SPEED UP OR ATTEMPT TO STALL.  VERY DANGEROUS ENTERING HIGH SPEED TRAFFIC SITUATIONS OR ACCELERATING IN LOCAL TRAFFIC.

WE BOUGHT A USED 2016 ATS WITH 14,000 MILES. WITHIN 2 YEARS, WE HAVE HAD 4 CRACKED CADILLAC WHEELS. WE ALSO HAVE RUN FLAT TIRES, FACTORY INSTALLED. DRIVING UNDER NORMAL CONDITIONS, POT HOLES AND SEAMS IN ASPHALT SEEM TO BE WHAT CAUSED OF CRACKED RIMS. I SUSPECTED A DEFECTIVE ISSUE AFTER 2ND CRACKED WHEEL. I ASKED AT LOCAL DEALERSHIP ABOUT A RECALL AND THEY SAID THEY DIDN'T SEE ONE. I SEE A NUMBER OF COMPLAINTS ONLINE AND FINALLY FOUND A COMPLAINT THROUGH CARCOMPLAINTS.COM THAT WAS NOTED ON NHTSA. THIS IS  A KNOWN ISSUE, FACTORY DEFECT AT CANNON CADILLAC IN LAKELAND, FL. IF DRIVEN ON RUN FLATS APPROX 15 MILES TO REPAIR FACILITY, TIRES CAN ALSO BE DAMAGED AND HAVE TO BE REPLACED WHICH WAS MY SITUATION. MY LAST WHEEL PURCHASED LASTED ME 1 YR, 3 WEEKS AND CRACKED BECAUSE OF SEAM IN ASPHALT ON THE FREEWAY. THIS NEEDS TO BE A RECALL. I NOW HAVE 35K MILES AND I'M LOOKING AT THE EXPENSE OF REPLACING ALL 4 WHEELS DUE TO CADILLAC STANDING BEHIND THIS DEFECTIVE WHEEL

WHILE DRIVING ON THE FREEWAY, A CAR WAS MERGING INTO MY LANE. I QUICKLY TURNED INTO THE NEXT AVAILABLE LANE AS IT WAS EMPTY, AND WHEN I TURNED THE STEERING WHEEL SLIGHTLY TO THE LEFT, IT OVERCOMPENSATED AND VIOLENTLY TURNED THE STEERING WHEEL TO THE LEFT, LEADING TO THE CAR SPINNING OUT ON THE FREEWAY. IT WAS DIFFICULT TO STRAIGHTEN THE WHEEL AT THAT POINT, UNTIL IT OVERCOMPENSATED TO THE RIGHT CAUSING ME TO SPIN OUT SOME MORE. THIS LED TO AN ACCIDENT, AND IT WAS A MIRACLE NO ONE WAS KILLED.     DURING THE TIME OF THIS ACCIDENT, THE ROAD WAS IN GOOD SHAPE, VISIBILITY WAS GOOD, THE WEATHER WAS GOOD, IT WAS AROUND 60 DEGREES OUTSIDE, I HAD JUST GOT ON TO THE FREEWAY, AND WAS TRAVELLING AROUND 60 MPH WHEN THIS HAPPENED (I.E. NO SPEEDING), AND I WAS DRIVING WITH MY LEFT ARM (IT IS A MANUAL, AND MY RIGHT HAND WAS NOT ON THE STEERING WHEEL AT THE TIME) AND DUE TO THE POSITIONING (MY LEFT ARM RESTING ON THE ARMREST), IT WOULD HAVE BEEN IMPOSSIBLE FOR ME TO HAVE TURNED THE STEERING WHEEL ENOUGH TO HAVE SPUN OUT.

issues.title: V6 Twin-Turbo Engine Carbon Buildup
issues.description: The LF4 3.6L twin-turbo V6 engine experiences significant carbon buildup on intake valves due to direct injection design, causing reduced performance and rough idle
issues.fix_description: Professional walnut blasting or chemical cleaning of intake valves, may require intake manifold removal
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, perform regular Italian tune-ups (high RPM driving), consider periodic intake cleaning service

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: Wastegate actuators develop rattle noise, particularly noticeable at idle and light acceleration, caused by worn wastegate components
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger wastegate actuator or entire turbocharger assembly depending on severity
issues.prevention: Use high-quality oil, avoid lugging the engine, allow proper warm-up and cool-down periods

issues.title: Timing Chain Stretch and Tensioner Issues
issues.description: Timing chain stretch and tensioner failure can occur prematurely, potentially causing catastrophic engine damage if chain jumps timing
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chains, tensioners, guides, and related components; may require engine removal
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid extended oil change intervals, monitor for early symptoms

issues.title: Fuel System High Pressure Pump Failure
issues.description: High-pressure fuel pump fails causing fuel starvation, poor performance, and potential engine damage under load
issues.fix_description: Replace high-pressure fuel pump and potentially low-pressure pump, clean fuel system
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, replace fuel filter regularly, avoid running tank very low

issues.title: CUE Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: Cadillac User Experience (CUE) system experiences frequent freezing, slow response, and complete system failures
issues.fix_description: Software updates, CUE module replacement, or complete infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid using system immediately after startup, gentle screen cleaning

issues.title: Differential Rear Cover Leak
issues.description: Rear differential cover develops leaks due to inadequate seal design, causing gear oil loss and potential differential damage
issues.fix_description: Replace differential cover gasket, inspect for warped cover, refill with proper gear oil
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of differential area, avoid aggressive launches, check fluid levels periodically

issues.title: Brake Pad Premature Wear
issues.description: Brembo brake pads wear excessively fast, particularly front pads, due to aggressive compound and driving style sensitivity
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads with OEM or performance aftermarket pads, inspect rotors for damage
issues.prevention: Moderate braking habits, regular brake inspections, avoid riding brakes

issues.title: Suspension Magnetic Ride Control Failure
issues.description: Magnetic Ride Control dampers fail, causing poor ride quality and suspension warning messages
issues.fix_description: Replace failed magnetic dampers, recalibrate suspension system
issues.prevention: Avoid harsh impacts, regular suspension inspections, protect from road salt corrosion

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption beyond normal levels, requiring frequent top-offs between oil changes
issues.fix_description: Diagnose source of consumption, may require piston rings, valve seals, or turbo seals replacement
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use proper oil viscosity, avoid extended high-RPM operation when cold

issues.title: Transmission Harsh Shifting
issues.description: 8-speed automatic transmission exhibits harsh or delayed shifts, particularly during cold weather or aggressive driving
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update, fluid change, or internal component replacement depending on severity
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, allow proper warm-up, avoid aggressive shifting when cold

issues.title: Heat Exchanger Coolant Leak
issues.description: Intercooler heat exchanger develops internal or external leaks, causing coolant loss and potential overheating
issues.fix_description: Replace heat exchanger unit, flush cooling system, pressure test for additional leaks
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, use proper coolant mixture, avoid overheating conditions

issues.title: Starter Motor Failure
issues.description: Starter motor fails prematurely, often due to heat soak from turbochargers, causing no-start conditions
issues.fix_description: Replace starter motor, inspect wiring and connections, test charging system
issues.prevention: Allow engine cool-down periods, maintain battery health, avoid excessive cranking attempts

editorial.tagline: American fury meets German precision in luxury armor
editorial.hero_blurb: The ATS-V represents Cadillac's bold declaration that American luxury can dance with the best from Bavaria and Stuttgart. This twin-turbo terror delivers 464 horsepower through one of the most sophisticated chassis ever to wear Cadillac's crest.
editorial.essence: The ATS-V is Cadillac's surgical strike against German sport sedan dominance, combining twin-turbo brutality with magnetic ride control wizardry. It's the rare luxury performance car that prioritizes driving engagement over comfort, making no apologies for its aggressive character.
editorial.heritage: Born from Cadillac's V-Series renaissance, the ATS-V builds on lessons learned from the CTS-V while targeting the BMW M3 and Mercedes C63 AMG directly. It represents the brand's commitment to reclaiming performance credibility in the compact luxury segment.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers crafted an aggressive yet refined aesthetic that balances luxury appointments with track-ready functionality. Every line serves dual purposes - looking purposeful while managing airflow and aerodynamics for serious performance driving.
editorial.motorsport_history: The ATS-V Coupe competed in IMSA's Continental Tire SportsCar Challenge, proving its track credentials against purpose-built race cars. This racing pedigree directly influenced the production car's suspension tuning and aerodynamic package.
editorial.engine_character: The twin-turbo V6 delivers immediate, crushing torque with a surprisingly linear power delivery that belies its forced induction. It's an engine that rewards aggression with savage acceleration while maintaining refinement during casual driving.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed automatic shifts with Germanic precision when left alone, but truly shines in manual mode with paddle shifters that deliver satisfying, quick-fire gear changes. Rev-matching on downshifts adds theatrical flair to spirited driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Magnetic Ride Control creates a Jekyll and Hyde personality - comfortable enough for daily duties yet capable of track-day precision when pushed. The chassis communicates clearly, building confidence through progressive, predictable responses.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted steering provides excellent on-center feel with weight that builds naturally as cornering forces increase. While not the most communicative rack, it offers precision and consistency that inspire confidence at the limit.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo brakes deliver incredible stopping power with excellent modulation and fade resistance. The pedal feel is firm and progressive, providing the kind of confidence needed for track work or aggressive street driving.
editorial.sound_signature: The exhaust note is distinctly American muscle with a modern twist - growling at idle, snarling under acceleration, with turbo whistles adding complexity. Performance exhaust modes transform it from civilized to savage with the touch of a button.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance-focused drivers who want German-level dynamics wrapped in American luxury, with enough daily usability for regular commuting. Perfect for those who prioritize driving engagement over ultimate comfort.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking maximum luxury comfort, those wanting naturally aspirated engine character, or drivers who rarely explore the car's performance capabilities. The firm ride and aggressive tuning won't suit comfort-first buyers.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with maintenance records and avoid early 2016 models with potential cooling system issues. The manual transmission is incredibly rare and valuable, while Recaro seats and Carbon Fiber packages are highly desirable options.
pros: Magnetic Ride Control delivers track capability
cons: Firm ride quality even in comfort mode
Limited rear seat and cargo space
